                    role="h3"><fo:inline role="a" id="Tasks"/>Tasks</fo:block><fo:block
                    space-before="1em" space-after="1em" role="p"/>We need to address the 'free' cam
                access issue - yes, students can attend any lecture, but does this translate to
                allowing everyone to see everything (including other student's discussions or first
                draft Wiki)? This should be agreed at a University level, and not be agreed by
                default by the University Computing Services, CARET or whoever has technical
                permissions. Oxford's <fo:inline role="span">
                    <fo:external-graphic src="url('http://localhost:8080/sakai-rwiki/images/icklearrow.gif')" role="img"/>
                    <fo:basic-link text-decoration="underline" color="blue" role="a"
                        external-destination="url('http://localhost:8080/access/content/group/c50c4b08-d361-4ccc-00e1-986782b05aef/OpensourceVLE.pdf')"
